00042 typedef struct CustomDataLayer {
00043     int type;       /* type of data in layer */
00044     int offset;     /* in editmode, offset of layer in block */
00045     int flag;       /* general purpose flag */
00046     int active;     /* number of the active layer of this type */
00047     int active_rnd; /* number of the layer to render*/
00048     int active_clone; /* number of the layer to render*/
00049     int active_mask; /* number of the layer to render*/
00050     int uid;        /* shape keyblock unique id reference*/
00051     char name[64];  /* layer name, MAX_CUSTOMDATA_LAYER_AAME */
00052     void *data;     /* layer data */
00053 } CustomDataLayer;

00064 typedef struct CustomData {
00065     CustomDataLayer *layers;      /* CustomDataLayers, ordered by type */
00066     int typemap[34];              /* runtime only! - maps types to indices of first layer of that type,
00067                                    * MUST be >= CD_NUMTYPES, but we cant use a define here.
00068                                    * Correct size is ensured in CustomData_update_typemap assert() */
00069 
00070     int totlayer, maxlayer;       /* number of layers, size of layers array */
00071     int totsize, pad2;             /* in editmode, total size of all data layers */
00072     void *pool;                   /* Bmesh: Memory pool for allocation of blocks */
00073     CustomDataExternal *external; /* external file storing customdata layers */
00074 } CustomData;

00154 /* CustomData.flag */

00156 /* indicates layer should not be copied by CustomData_from_template or
00157  * CustomData_copy_data */
00158 #define CD_FLAG_NOCOPY    (1<<0)
00159 /* indicates layer should not be freed (for layers backed by external data) */
00160 #define CD_FLAG_NOFREE    (1<<1)
00161 /* indicates the layer is only temporary, also implies no copy */
00162 #define CD_FLAG_TEMPORARY ((1<<2)|CD_FLAG_NOCOPY)
00163 /* indicates the layer is stored in an external file */
00164 #define CD_FLAG_EXTERNAL  (1<<3)
00165 /* indicates external data is read into memory */
00166 #define CD_FLAG_IN_MEMORY (1<<4)
